## 4. Neural Ordinary Differential Equations (Neural ODEs)

Instead of learning discrete steps or penalizing residuals, Neural ODEs parameterize the continuous derivative itself:

$$
\frac{d\mathbf{h}(t)}{dt} = f_\theta(\mathbf{h}(t), t)
$$

The forward pass becomes an initial value problem (IVP) solved by a black-box ODE solver (e.g., explicit Runge-Kutta). This constrains the network to learn a smooth, continuous vector field. However, training with a pointwise Mean Squared Error (MSE) loss in a chaotic regime often forces the model to collapse into a "safe" limit cycle to avoid massive phase-shift penalties.

